# Managed by envi (integrations/ssh/config). Included from ~/.ssh/config.
#
# Connection multiplexing (ControlMaster)
# =======================================
# The first interactive ssh to a host opens a long-lived "master" socket under
# ~/.ssh/cm/. Any later ssh to the SAME target (from any shell, e.g. an AI agent
# via `erun`) reuses that already-authenticated connection as a new channel, with
# no re-auth: no key, no password, no 2FA prompt.
#
# This is what lets an agent run commands on hosts YOU opened interactively,
# including hosts the agent has never seen and has no credentials for. You do the
# human auth once (password / 2FA / jump host); the agent piggybacks on it.
#
# - ControlPath uses %C (a hash of user+host+port), so the socket path never
#   exceeds the ~104-char unix-socket limit, even for long FQDNs or ProxyJump.
# - ControlPersist keeps the master alive for 30m after the last client exits,
#   so the agent can keep working briefly after you close the interactive pane.
Host *
    ControlMaster auto
    ControlPath ~/.ssh/cm/%C
    ControlPersist 30m
